Wanna know how to make god laugh? Tell him about your plans.. :)
&nbsp;
.. I'm still planning on dropping out for good this time. Nothing has changed with this year's classes, even with the new teachers. The classes are of no use to me .. I'm still merely borrowing time and money to survive.
&nbsp;
I'd have to find some way to live on 200NZD a week (145USD). Then just live on the absolute bare minimum .. growing vegetables, canning food. Mine cryptocurrency as a supplement. Grow and sell cannabis, if I have to. Hunt down online scammers and fraudsters for sport .. infect their servers with cryptocurrency miners. Just do absolutely anything that it takes to get the free time that I need to pursue my passion projects.. well, except ask for donations. I don't want to become a criminal .. my aspiration is to be more of an innovator, pioneer .. but yeeaahhh, being a pioneer doesn't pay the bills .. so this would be one way of funding my leisure time.
&nbsp;
..I don't know .. I guess I'd rather sell some sacks and hunt down mobsters, than ask for donations. Donations don't seem to give you that same 'breadwinner buzz', so to speak. They can also be somewhat influencing .. I'd hate to think that I have to 100% live up to a donor's expectations. I like to give and contribute, but I don't wanna be a people-pleaser. 
&nbsp;
My original plan of living off the grid may have sounded far-fetched .. but that doesn't mean you can't find a sweet spot in the middle.. and just slowly withdraw from this suckass society, like coming off of an opiate. Getting out of the comfort zone. 
&nbsp;
Of course, the only way to abandon the comfort zone is to realize that it's no longer a comfort zone. I've already tried fitting in with the corporate, full-time 9-5 life .. about a dozen times .. for about 7 years now .. and it didn't pan out. I've tried college .. and that, too .. is slowly beginning to eat me up, despite having felt excited about it for the first couple of months. Living in this society has become like a crippling terminal disease, and I have to act quickly.
&nbsp;
My high school friend just came to visit me yesterday, too. It was his weekend off. He was wearing pajamas in his car .. driving around aimlessly, ordering takeaways. All I could remember coming out of this mouth were the words: 'I hate my job'. 
&nbsp;
From that moment, I thought to myself  .. man, I don't ever wanna be like that. Work 9-5, come home .. be all tired as fuck, have no energy to work on the things you love. Eat takeaway, drink beer. Fall asleep. Rinse and repeat. Fuck that shit. 
&nbsp;
Now that I already have a good enough PC, I can continue working on my deep learning projects. Build robots. Build drones. Buy a 3d printer. That's all I wanna do .. and I wanna do it 100% my way. Without anybody watching my back or telling me what time I need to get out of bed, what operating system I should use, how I should dress, how I should talk to customers, etc. My way.

