Sometimes I wish I could have been born in the US. You guys should consider yourselves lucky. 
&nbsp;
The minute you criticize Jacinda Ardern for raising taxes on fuel (supposedly as an attempt to save the environment..) .. you get treated like a misogynistic, sexist monster. You get called a racist for even suggesting that English should be the official language.
&nbsp;
.. this likely means that the conservatives will have the 2020 election in the bag. Labour will fail to provide the change that this country needs, and we will be back to square zero. Back to the way things were in 2010. And the minute you warn them of this, you take an even harder beating .. and they downvote the fuck out of you.
&nbsp;
This actually really hurts to see. Maybe this could be my motivation to get the fuck out of this country, and maybe apply for IT jobs in America .. start over. I hate the 9-5 corporate world, but I'd be willing to grind it out with clenching teeth .. if it means not having to be here in this depressing backwater. I know you guys have Trump .. but trust me .. Trump is a gift in disguise. Trump will pave the way for better politicians in future. If we had a Trump here in New Zealand, I'd vote for him any time. 
&nbsp;
I agree with Julian Assange now.. sorry that it took me a while. It looks like he did have a valid point. Establishment politics needs to die, first and foremost. If it means electing some jackass just to spark the flame of revolution, then so be it.
&nbsp;
Having said that, I'm not making any immediate plans. I'll keep doing what I'm doing, keep smuggin'. Just live in the moment, lead by example. Adopt anarchism as a way of life. Work hard on the things that matter to me. You gotta work hard, even if you hate the idea of having a job. You gotta have sickening work ethic to get anything done, especially the things you are passionate about.
&nbsp;
I still love this country, but man .. these people need to have some cold water dropped on them.

I have to admit, I haven't been doing anything for the past couple of days. I sat through one class in college, and then went straight back home .. just to sleep all evening. I skipped college today, and have mainly been browsing twitter.. but I feel just as unenthusiastic as yesterday, although nowhere near as bad.
&nbsp;
The political sphere seems to be so disintegrated and chaotic right now, it no longer makes sense to pick a side. You can, however, side with individuals - and in my eyes, Assange represents Revolution. I wouldn't care if he were secretly a Trump supporter, or a Putin supporter .. Putin and Trump are merely political tricksters, and we kinda need them in order to call out the hypocrisies of neoliberalism .. as awful and tyrannical as they may seem. Putin has also recently spoken out against the shooting of protestors at Gaza.
